<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 5000, 9100, 9200, 9400, AND 9900 MODELS - HEATER AND AIR
        CONDITIONER - TROUBLESHOOTING
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>TROUBLESHOOTING</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <seqlist style="alphauc">
                <item>
                    <para>Before beginning these test procedures, make sure the vehicle batteries are at 75% state of
                        charge (SOC) or higher. This represents an open circuit voltage (OCV) of 13.4 volts. Batteries
                        with an OCV of 12 volts or less are either completely discharged or have a dead cell.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Before beginning these test procedures, check any light or indicator lamp filaments that are
                        suspected of being open (burned out). This is done to avoid unnecessary extensive circuit
                        checks.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Before beginning these test procedures, inspect all connectors for loose or damaged pins,
                        wires, etc. Refer to TEST EQUIPMENT AND CONNECTOR REPAIR section in GROUP 08 - ELECTRICAL in the
                        CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>When the technician determines that a fuse is blown, while checking its condition, he is
                        directed to locate the cause of the overload condition and to repair it. While no further
                        instruction on this procedure is listed in the diagnostic tables, the common procedure is as
                        follows: isolate sections of the circuit, by disconnecting connectors, and measure the
                        resistance to ground to find the circuit that is shorted to ground. Then locate the damaged spot
                        in the wire or connector and repair.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Diagnostics for circuits that are malfunctioning by sticking in the on position are generally
                        not covered in detail. It is assumed that the technician knows to check for a malfunctioning
                        switch, relay, or solenoid.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
            <title>Air Conditioner With Day Cab and Box Sleeper</title>
            <table id="t0820501" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Air Conditioner With Day Cab and Box Sleeper</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.70in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth=".75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.79in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.58in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Check fuse F1-B for open condition.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>F1-B.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair. Replace fuse.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Measure voltage at fuse F1-B circuit 77T to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>F1-B, 77T to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 77T, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off/ On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Turn ignition off and disconnect connector (162). Turn ignition and A/C on and
                                    measure voltage at (162) from circuit 77H to ground.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>(162), 77H to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 77H, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off/ On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Turn ignition off and reconnect connector (162). Turn ignition on and at manual
                                    temperature control switch, measure voltage from circuit 77B to gnd.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Temp control ,77B to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 77B, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Make sure evaporator is above 38&#176;F (3.5&#176;C). At the manual temperature
                                    control switch, measure voltage from circuit 77A to ground.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Temp control, 77A to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace defective manual temperature control switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off/ On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>With ignition switch off, remove A/C relay (463-R6). Turn ignition switch on, and
                                    at relay socket, measure voltage from circuit 77A to gnd.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(463- R6), 77A to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 77A, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>7.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off/ On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>With ignition switch off, install a test jumper at relay socket (463-R6) from
                                    circuit 77A to 77C. Disconnect circuit 77C from refrigerant compressor clutch, and
                                    turn ignition switch on. At circuit 77C, measure voltage to ground.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>By compressor, 77C to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 77C from A/C relay, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>8.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Reconnect circuit 77C to refrigerant compressor clutch. Can the clutch be heard
                                    engaging?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace defective refrigerant compressor clutch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>9.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off/On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>With ignition switch off, disconnect circuit 77C from low pressure safety switch.
                                    Turn ignition switch on and measure voltage from circuit 77C to gnd.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Near low press. switch, 77C to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 77C from (162), then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>10.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off/ On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>With ignition switch off, disconnect circuit 77E from high pressure safety switch.
                                    Turn ignition switch on and measure voltage from circuit 77E to gnd.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Near high press. switch, 77E to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 77E, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>11.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>With A/C switch on and temperature switch set to cool, measure voltage from
                                    circuit 77A to 77-G at relay socket (463-R6).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>(463- R6), 77A to 77-G.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 77-G, 58-GA, or 11-G to right dash gnd
                                    stud, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>12.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At socket (463-R6) measure resistance of circuit 77D.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>(463- R6), 77D, B to C/77D to 77D.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 77D, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>13.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off/ On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Install a test jumper at relay socket (463-R6) from circuit 77A to 77F. Turn
                                    ignition switch on and at low pressure safety switch and circuit 77F, measure
                                    voltage to ground.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Low press. switch 77F to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 77F from A/C relay, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>14.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At high pressure safety switch and circuit 77J, measure voltage to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>High press. switch, 77J to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 77J, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>15.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Measure resistance of low pressure safety switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Across low press. switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Verify that refrigerant charge is greater than 40 psi, then replace defective low
                                    pressure switch.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>16.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Measure resistance of high pressure safety switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Across high press. switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Verify that refrigerant charge is less than 150 psi, then replace defective high
                                    pressure switch.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>17.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Bench test A/C relay by measuring resistance from terminal 30 to 87A.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>A/C relay, 30 to 87A.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace defective relay.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>18.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Bench test A/C relay by applying + 12 volts to pin 86, ground to pin 85, and
                                    measuring resistance from terminal 30 to 87.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Energized A/C relay, 30 to 87.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace defective relay.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>19.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Air conditioner circuits check good. Remove test jumpers, re-install relay, and
                                    reconnect the separated connector.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcproc>
